I will go back to Huanggang as soon as the city is lifted, and I want to talk to my wife,"said Hu.

2,675 words, about 5 minutes to read

Hu Anping pseudonym will be discharged after the day known as the "second life. ".

Hu Anping, a 53-year-old native of Huanggang, Hubei Province, runs a poultry business in the Huanggang Vegetable Market. At the end of December, he was admitted to the intensive-care unit at COVID-19 after being diagnosed with severe pneumonia. On January 28, he was officially discharged. Earlier reports said he was the first critically ill patient to be released from the hospital following the Wuhan outbreak.

Today, Hu remains in self-imposed quarantine at a hotel in Wuhan. He doesn't go out, stays in his hotel every day to catch the news, and is most concerned about the progress of the epidemic. His son bought him bread, biscuits and instant noodles, while his wife stayed at home in Huanggang and called him three times a day to let him know she was safe. "I'll go back to Huanggang as soon as Wuhan is lifted, and I want to talk to my wife, " he said.

━━━━━

I didn't sleep for two days and two nights before I went to the intensive-care unit

Beijing News: When did the symptoms appear?

Hu Anping: At the end of December 2019, I developed cold symptoms, cold body, at home to cover three quilts. Because usually my physical fitness is good, just a little high blood pressure. I was busy at home and didn't go to the hospital right away. It took me days to get comfortable before I went to Huanggang Central. CT SCAN showed pneumonia, a shadow on his right lung, and he was hospitalized that day.

Two days in the hospital injection, the third day to film, left lung infection. The attending doctor called my wife over, said my condition was a bit serious, and prepared a "serious illness notice" for the family to sign. My wife was nervous because a few years ago a relative in our family had kidney failure from a persistent high fever. So we talked about turning to Wuhan for treatment. At 4:00 pm on January 5, the Central Hospital contacted the ambulance and pulled me to Wuhan Zhongnan Hospital.

Beijing News: How was the examination in Wuhan Hospital?

Hu Anping: When I arrived in Wuhan, several large hospitals in Wuhan were already full of patients. There's a lot of patients at central south. Before I came to Wuhan, I knew that the south China seafood market had been closed, someone had been infected, and I ran a poultry business in Huanggang. Although I have never been to the south China Seafood Market, most of the seafood in the market comes from south China. Or how I got it. We didn't know what it was, only that it affected the lungs. After being transferred to Wuhan, he was also treated according to the diagnosis of pneumonia. Later, the doctor told me that I had "new type of coronary pneumonia" , I was the first batch of patients, did not know how to treat, also do not know what to use drugs.

On January 6, the doctor began to examine me, draw blood, took a CT, at that time, my two lungs have been white, the doctor said I was just in time, another two days to drag into a "dead lung. ".

More than a dozen doctors diagnosed, saw the film, said my lungs have formed a "white lung" , left and right lung shadow, very serious. I was having trouble breathing and had a fever of 102. On January 7, I moved into the intensive-care unit.

I hadn't slept for almost two days and nights before I went to the intensive-care unit. I can't go to sleep. I'm afraid if I fall asleep, I won't wake up. When I came in after the procedure, my mind was clear. My family encouraged me, said no matter how much money will give me treatment, will be waiting for me.

Beijing News: How is IT TREATED IN INTENSIVE-CARE UNIT?

Hu Anping: My family asked someone outside the hospital to buy me some imported medicine. There are five bottles in a group, each bottle costs 700 yuan. I use one group every day, that's 3,500 yuan a day. Then three more doses of another imported drug, for less than $20,000. Anti-inflammatory needle water hanging from morning to night, almost never broken.

I spent three days in the intensive-care unit before I felt anything. I was still cold. The nurse came to see me, and I couldn't talk through the respirator, so I had to use my fingers to get her to give me an extra quilt.

My family came to see me every day and bought noodles and dumplings. But they can't go into the ward. The food comes through the nurse. The doctor told me that I must force myself to eat. The most obvious symptoms of this disease are bitter mouth and weak limbs. I couldn't even pick up a dumpling for dinner that day, so I had to let the nurse feed me. I was worried I was GONNA be crippled forever.

"The doctor said I was a second-time Freshman. "

Beijing News: How effective is the treatment?

Juan Ping: Luckily the treatment worked for me. I recovered well, and on the fourth day, the doctor pulled the plug and let me breathe by myself, but still for an hour or two a day. And get a C.T. my lungs are almost fully functional. The attending doctors and nurses gave me thumbs-up, all said that I was in good health, praised me strong will. How can I not be strong? I have a wife and kids to take care of.

Beijing News: What Happened Next?

Hu Anping: On the 5th and 6th day, I began to speak a little, and I was able to eat, but I still had no energy and could not move. Catheter in, urine and feces on the bed, wheelchair everywhere you go.

I practice hard in bed every day, clenching my hands and stretching them, moving my feet as well. After two or three days of practice, I could eat with my hands. The doctor told me to practice writing, so I forced myself to write and moved my feet a little. The doctor saw that my recovery is not bad, and asked me to take a CT, take the film, he said that my lung function is almost recovered, the body temperature is normal. On January 17th, the doctor said I could be transferred to the general ward.

Beijing News: In the General Ward What treatment to carry out?

Hu Anping: Even though I was transferred to the General Ward, I still had a dry cough, I was weak all over, I couldn't move my hands or feet, and I was still in a wheelchair. I'm quarantined in the General Ward, and I'm on a daily I.V. drip. Daily physical examination, oral biological standard test, blood pressure, blood lipids, heart rate, detection of stool and urine and so on. Take your temperature twice a day, once in the morning and once in the afternoon, and draw blood every other day.

Beijing News: How's your health?

Hu Anping: Still Weak, I practice standing alone in the ward with a chair and a window frame every day. I can't stand without something to support me. After a few days of practice, I began to walk slowly without holding anything. On the third CT SCAN, the doctor said my lungs were fully functional and my temperature was normal, so that's a recovery. The doctors said it was my second birth.

After recovery there is a quarantine period, I stayed in south-central hospital for another week, but the hospital more and more patients, beds are too tight. So I was discharged on the fourth day of the first lunar month.

Wuhan has my relatives and friends, but I know I have this disease is infectious, dare not go to other people's homes, in the hotel self-isolation, to now have 15 days. Son in the next room to live with me, every day to buy bread, biscuits, instant noodles, I dare not go out, for fear of affecting others.

"When I'm cured, I'll have a few more months with my family and friends. "

Beijing News: What do you do every day now?

Hu An Ping: Every day in the hotel, brush the mobile phone, watch the news, sometimes also brush Douyin, watch video entertainment. The first thing I do when I wake up every day is to see if there are any new cases, new drugs, etc. . My wife calls me three times a day, morning, noon and night, and we tell each other we're safe.

Beijing News: What are your plans after that?

Hu Anping: When the city of Wuhan is lifted and the quarantine period is over, I will go back to Huanggang. Friends and relatives know that I have this disease, I will definitely have scruples, customers may not dare to patronize my booth, I can understand. I also told them, although I am now cured, but do not come to see me for two months, until the virus has been completely eliminated, I do not want to harm them. It's GonNa be a few more months between us.

Beijing News: What do you want to do after you go home?

Hu Anping: I want to talk to my wife, I miss her so much. Trying to get in touch with family and friends. I came to Wuhan, the mobile phone at home did not bring out, the current mobile phone or the son recently to buy. I am sick, a lot of relatives and friends must worry about me, I go back to call them one by one, tell them the situation.

Beijing News: Do you have any suggestions for the patients who are still in treatment?

Hu Anping: in addition to cooperating with the doctor, we must keep a good attitude. When I first got out of the hospital, I had a sore throat and had trouble speaking. But I practiced speaking and sometimes singing every day during the quarantine at the hotel, and I'm almost fine now.

Hu Jie, editor, Hsinking Daily News
